THE Special Adviser to Governor Ben Ayade on Biodiversity, Edet Asim, is dead. Asim, who was a former chairman of Calabar Municipal Council, reportedly slumped and died in his car, in Calabar on Tuesday. The cause of his death has been linked to heart attack, though there has not been an official report to that effect. While his remains were said to have been deposited at the morgue, details of his burial have not been communicated officially by family members.  Details later.. 